#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:11
msgid "Setting Up the Environment"
msgstr "Configurando o Ambiente"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:13
msgid ""
"Set up a good working environment by creating two new startup files for the "
"<command>bash</command> shell. While logged in as user <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>, issue the following command to create a "
"new <filename>.bash_profile</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Configure um bom ambiente de trabalho criando dois novos arquivos de "
"inicialização para o shell <command>bash</command>. Enquanto logada(o) como "
"usuária(o) <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>, emita o seguinte "
"comando para criar um novo <filename>.bash_profile</filename>:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; ~/.bash_profile &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>exec env -i HOME=$HOME TERM=$TERM PS1='\\u:\\w\\$ ' /bin/bash</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; ~/.bash_profile &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>exec env -i HOME=$HOME TERM=$TERM PS1='\\u:\\w\\$ ' /bin/bash</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:22
msgid ""
"When logged on as user <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>, or "
"when switched to the &lfs-user; user using an <command>su</command> command "
"with the <quote><parameter>-</parameter></quote> option, the initial shell "
"is a <emphasis>login</emphasis> shell which reads the <filename>/etc/"
"profile</filename> of the host (probably containing some settings and "
"environment variables) and then <filename>.bash_profile</filename>.  The "
"<command>exec env -i.../bin/bash</command> command in the <filename>."
"bash_profile</filename> file replaces the running shell with a new one with "
"a completely empty environment, except for the <envar>HOME</envar>, "
"<envar>TERM</envar>, and <envar>PS1</envar> variables. This ensures that no "
"unwanted and potentially hazardous environment variables from the host "
"system leak into the build environment."
msgstr ""
"Enquanto logada(o) como usuária(o) <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</"
"systemitem> ou quando alternado para o(a) usuário(a) &lfs-user; usando um "
"comando <command>su</command> com a opção <quote><parameter>-</parameter></"
"quote>, o shell inicial é um shell de <emphasis>login</emphasis> que lê o "
"<filename>/etc/profile</filename> do anfitrião (provavelmente contendo "
"algumas configurações e variáveis de ambiente) e então <filename>."
"bash_profile</filename>. O comando <command>exec env -i.../bin/bash</"
"command> no arquivo <filename>.bash_profile</filename> substitui o shell em "
"execução por um novo com um ambiente completamente vazio, exceto pelas "
"variáveis <envar>HOME</envar>, <envar>TERM</envar> e <envar>PS1</envar>. "
"Isso garante que nenhuma variável de ambiente indesejada e potencialmente "
"danosa oriunda do sistema anfitrião vaze para o ambiente de construção."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:35
msgid ""
"The new instance of the shell is a <emphasis>non-login</emphasis> shell, "
"which does not read, and execute, the contents of the <filename>/etc/"
"profile</filename> or <filename>.bash_profile</filename> files, but rather "
"reads, and executes, the <filename>.bashrc</filename> file instead. Create "
"the <filename>.bashrc</filename> file now:"
msgstr ""
"A nova instância do shell é um shell de <emphasis>não-login</emphasis>, que "
"não lê, e executa, o conteúdo dos arquivos <filename>/etc/profile</filename> "
"ou <filename>.bash_profile</filename>, porém, ao invés, lê, e executa, o "
"arquivo <filename>.bashrc</filename>. Crie o arquivo <filename>.bashrc</"
"filename> agora:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:41
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; ~/.bashrc &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>set +h\n"
"umask 022\n"
"LFS=/mnt/lfs\n"
"LC_ALL=POSIX\n"
"LFS_TGT=$(uname -m)-lfs-linux-gnu\n"
"PATH=/usr/bin\n"
"if [ ! -L /bin ]; then PATH=/bin:$PATH; fi\n"
"PATH=$LFS/tools/bin:$PATH\n"
"CONFIG_SITE=$LFS/usr/share/config.site\n"
"export LFS LC_ALL LFS_TGT PATH CONFIG_SITE</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; ~/.bashrc &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>set +h\n"
"umask 022\n"
"LFS=/mnt/lfs\n"
"LC_ALL=POSIX\n"
"LFS_TGT=$(uname -m)-lfs-linux-gnu\n"
"PATH=/usr/bin\n"
"if [ ! -L /bin ]; then PATH=/bin:$PATH; fi\n"
"PATH=$LFS/tools/bin:$PATH\n"
"CONFIG_SITE=$LFS/usr/share/config.site\n"
"export LFS LC_ALL LFS_TGT PATH CONFIG_SITE</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><title>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:55
msgid "The meaning of the settings in <filename>.bashrc</filename>"
msgstr "O significado das configurações em <filename>.bashrc</filename>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:58
msgid "<parameter>set +h</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>set +h</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:60
msgid ""
"The <command>set +h</command> command turns off <command>bash</command>'s "
"hash function. Hashing is ordinarily a useful feature&mdash;<command>bash</"
"command> uses a hash table to remember the full path to executable files to "
"avoid searching the <envar>PATH</envar> time and again to find the same "
"executable. However, the new tools should be used as soon as they are "
"installed. Switching off the hash function forces the shell to search the "
"<envar>PATH</envar> whenever a program is to be run. As such, the shell will "
"find the newly compiled tools in <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools/"
"bin</filename> as soon as they are available without remembering a previous "
"version of the same program provided by the host distro, in <filename "
"class='directory'>/usr/bin</filename> or <filename class='directory'>/bin</"
"filename>."
msgstr ""
"O comando <command>set +h</command> desliga a função hash do <command>bash</"
"command>. “Hashing” geralmente é uma característica útil&mdash;"
"<command>bash</command> usa uma tabela hash para lembrar o caminho completo "
"para arquivos executáveis para evitar procurar o <envar>PATH</envar> várias "
"vezes para encontrar o mesmo executável. Entretanto, as novas ferramentas "
"deveriam ser usadas tão logo sejam instaladas. Alternando para desligada a "
"função hash força o shell a procurar no <envar>PATH</envar> sempre que um "
"aplicativo estiver para ser executado. Dessa forma, o shell encontrará as "
"ferramentas recém compiladas em <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools/"
"bin</filename> tão logo elas estejam disponíveis sem lembrar da versão "
"anterior do mesmo aplicativo fornecida pela distribuição anfitriã, em "
"<filename class='directory'>/usr/bin</filename> ou <filename "
"class='directory'>/bin</filename>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:77
msgid "<parameter>umask 022</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>umask 022</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:79
msgid ""
"Setting the user file-creation mask (umask) to 022 ensures that newly "
"created files and directories are only writable by their owner, but are "
"readable and executable by anyone (assuming default modes are used by the "
"<function>open(2)</function> system call, new files will end up with "
"permission mode 644 and directories with mode 755)."
msgstr ""
"Configurar a máscara de criação de arquivos do(a) usuário(a) (umask) para "
"022 garante que recém criados arquivos e diretórios são graváveis somente "
"por seus(uas) donos(as), mas são legíveis e executáveis por qualquer pessoa "
"(assumindo que os modos padrão são usados pelas chamadas de sistema "
"<function>open(2)</function>, novos arquivos terminarão com modo de "
"permissão 644 e diretórios com modo 755)."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:88
msgid "<parameter>LFS=/mnt/lfs</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>LFS=/mnt/lfs</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:90
msgid ""
"The <envar>LFS</envar> variable should be set to the chosen mount point."
msgstr ""
"A variável <envar>LFS</envar> deveria ser configurada para o ponto de "
"montagem escolhido."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:96
msgid "<parameter>LC_ALL=POSIX</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>LC_ALL=POSIX</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:98
msgid ""
"The <envar>LC_ALL</envar> variable controls the localization of certain "
"programs, making their messages follow the conventions of a specified "
"country.  Setting <envar>LC_ALL</envar> to <quote>POSIX</quote> or <quote>C</"
"quote> (the two are equivalent) ensures that everything will work as "
"expected in the cross-compilation environment."
msgstr ""
"A variável <envar>LC_ALL</envar> controla a localização de certos "
"aplicativos, fazendo suas mensagens seguirem as convenções de um país "
"especificado. Configurar <envar>LC_ALL</envar> para <quote>POSIX</quote> ou "
"<quote>C</quote> (as duas são equivalentes) garante que tudo vai funcionar "
"como esperado no ambiente de compilação cruzada."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:107
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "<parameter>LFS_TGT=(uname -m)-lfs-linux-gnu</parameter>"
msgid "<parameter>LFS_TGT=$(uname -m)-lfs-linux-gnu</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>LFS_TGT=(uname -m)-lfs-linux-gnu</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:109
msgid ""
"The <envar>LFS_TGT</envar> variable sets a non-default, but compatible "
"machine description for use when building our cross-compiler and linker and "
"when cross-compiling our temporary toolchain. More information is provided "
"by <xref linkend=\"ch-tools-toolchaintechnotes\" role=\"\"/>."
msgstr ""
"A variável <envar>LFS_TGT</envar> configura uma não padrão, porém compatível "
"descrição de máquina para uso quando da construção do nosso compilador "
"cruzado e vinculador e quando da compilação cruzada do nosso conjunto de "
"ferramentas temporárias. Mais informação é fornecida pelas <xref "
"linkend=\"ch-tools-toolchaintechnotes\" role=\"\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:117
msgid "<parameter>PATH=/usr/bin</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>PATH=/usr/bin</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:119
msgid ""
"Many modern Linux distributions have merged <filename class=\"directory\">/"
"bin</filename> and <filename class=\"directory\">/usr/bin</filename>. When "
"this is the case, the standard <envar>PATH</envar> variable should be set to "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/usr/bin/</filename> for the <xref "
"linkend=\"chapter-temporary-tools\"/> environment. When this is not the "
"case, the following line adds <filename class=\"directory\">/bin</filename> "
"to the path."
msgstr ""
"Muitas distribuições modernas do Linux mesclaram <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/bin</filename> e <filename class=\"directory\">/usr/"
"bin</filename>. Quando esse for o caso, a variável <envar>PATH</envar> "
"padrão deveria ser configurada para <filename class=\"directory\">/usr/bin/</"
"filename> para o ambiente do <xref linkend=\"chapter-temporary-tools\"/>. "
"Quando esse não for o caso, a seguinte linha acrescenta <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/bin</filename> ao caminho."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:131
msgid "<parameter>if [ ! -L /bin ]; then PATH=/bin:$PATH; fi</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>if [ ! -L /bin ]; then PATH=/bin:$PATH; fi</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:133
msgid ""
"If <filename class=\"directory\">/bin</filename> is not a symbolic link, it "
"must be added to the <envar>PATH</envar> variable."
msgstr ""
"Se <filename class=\"directory\">/bin</filename> não for um link simbólico, "
"[então] ele precisa ser acrescentado à variável <envar>PATH</envar>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:139
msgid "<parameter>PATH=$LFS/tools/bin:$PATH</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>PATH=$LFS/tools/bin:$PATH</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:141
msgid ""
"By putting <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools/bin</filename> ahead of "
"the standard <envar>PATH</envar>, the cross-compiler installed at the "
"beginning of <xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> is picked up by the "
"shell immediately after its installation. This, combined with turning off "
"hashing, limits the risk that the compiler from the host is used instead of "
"the cross-compiler."
msgstr ""
"Ao se colocar <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools/bin</filename> a "
"frente do <envar>PATH</envar> padrão, o compilador cruzado instalado no "
"início do <xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> é pego pelo shell "
"imediatamente depois da instalação dele. Isso, combinado com a desativação "
"do hashing, limita o risco de que o compilador originário do anfitrião seja "
"usado em vez do compilador cruzado."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:151
msgid "<parameter>CONFIG_SITE=$LFS/usr/share/config.site</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>CONFIG_SITE=$LFS/usr/share/config.site</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:153
msgid ""
"In <xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> and <xref linkend=\"chapter-"
"temporary-tools\"/>, if this variable is not set, <command>configure</"
"command> scripts may attempt to load configuration items specific to some "
"distributions from <filename>/usr/share/config.site</filename> on the host "
"system. Override it to prevent potential contamination from the host."
msgstr ""
"No <xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> e no <xref linkend=\"chapter-"
"temporary-tools\"/>, se essa variável não estiver configurada, [então] os "
"scripts <command>configure</command> possivelmente tentem carregar itens de "
"configuração específicos para algumas distribuições a partir de <filename>/"
"usr/share/config.site</filename> no sistema anfitrião. Substitua-o para "
"evitar uma potencial contaminação oriunda do anfitrião."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:163
msgid "<parameter>export ...</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>export ...</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:165
msgid ""
"While the preceding commands have set some variables, in order to make them "
"visible within any sub-shells, we export them."
msgstr ""
"Ao tempo que os comandos precedentes tenham configurado algumas variáveis, "
"com a finalidade de torná-las visíveis dentro de quaisquer sub-shells, nós "
"as exportamos."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><important><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:174
msgid ""
"Several commercial distributions add an undocumented instantiation of "
"<filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</filename> to the initialization of "
"<command>bash</command>. This file has the potential to modify the "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> user's environment in ways "
"that can affect the building of critical LFS packages. To make sure the "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> user's environment is clean, "
"check for the presence of <filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</filename> and, if "
"present, move it out of the way.  As the <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, run:"
msgstr ""
"Muitas distribuições comerciais acrescentam uma instância não documentada de "
"<filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</filename> à inicialização do <command>bash</"
"command>. Esse arquivo tem o potencial de modificar o ambiente do(a) "
"usuário(a) <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> de formas que "
"podem afetar a construção de pacotes LFS críticos. Para assegurar que o "
"ambiente do(a) usuário(a) <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> "
"esteja limpo, verifique a presença de <filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</filename> "
"e, se presente, mova-o para fora do caminho. Como o(a) usuário(a) "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, execute:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><important><screen>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>[ ! -e /etc/bash.bashrc ] || mv -v /etc/bash.bashrc /etc/bash.bashrc.NOUSE</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>[ ! -e /etc/bash.bashrc ] || mv -v /etc/bash.bashrc /etc/bash.bashrc.NOUSE</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><important><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:187
msgid ""
"When the <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> user is no longer "
"needed (at the beginning of <xref linkend=\"chapter-chroot-temporary-tools\"/"
">), you may safely restore <filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</filename> (if "
"desired)."
msgstr ""
"Quando o(a) usuário(a) <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> não "
"mais for necessária(o) (no início do <xref linkend=\"chapter-chroot-"
"temporary-tools\"/>), você pode seguramente restaurar <filename>/etc/bash."
"bashrc</filename> (se desejado)."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><important><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:192
msgid ""
"Note that the LFS Bash package we will build in <xref linkend=\"ch-system-"
"bash\"/> is not configured to load or execute <filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</"
"filename>, so this file is useless on a completed LFS system."
msgstr ""
"Perceba que o pacote Bash do LFS que nós construiremos na <xref linkend=\"ch-"
"system-bash\"/> não é configurado para carregar ou para executar <filename>/"
"etc/bash.bashrc</filename>, de modo que esse arquivo é inútil em um sistema "
"LFS finalizado."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:198
msgid ""
"Finally, to ensure the environment is fully prepared for building the "
"temporary tools, force the <command>bash</command> shell to read the new "
"user profile:"
msgstr ""
"Finalmente, para garantir que o ambiente esteja totalmente preparado para a "
"construção das ferramentas temporárias, force o shell <command>bash</"
"command> a ler o perfil do(a) novo(a) usuário(a):"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: lfs-en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:202
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>source ~/.bash_profile</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>source ~/.bash_profile</userinput>"
